Not only is their food spectacular....I am always shocked by the sushi they make and the price  they sell it for. I would gladly spend double the amount of money, but only for food with this level of quality. Aside from quality, the quantity alone is outstanding.  Superior food, large portions, great prices.... I have yet to figure out how they manage to make their sushi *ALWAYS FRESH* every single time I order, in record timing. It’s outstanding. But I think overall, considering I have only a select few “sushi places” that I am willing to go to......the one thing that no other restaurant has (within at least a 20 mile radius, literally) that Ichiban Sushi of Bowie DOES HAVE = stellar customer service.  The girl that works up front (I don’t want to throw out names) has been there for as long as I can remember. And she alone, has proven to be a major asset to this restaurant. I truly hope that her superiors and management recognize this and acknowledge it as well.  I think it’s awesome that someone her age, has the maturity and the drive to take the lead...not just in terms of creating a great reputation.  But she’s made a mark on that place that is financially beneficial and the reputation that they now have....will last a lifetime.  She has officially proven that “the customer is always right” theory, does not apply to every restaurant! Because I can promise you, if there’s any “problem” when ordering from this place.....the customer is definitely wrong.  Especially if the customers name is Karen😂  Seriously, this girl needs a raise before another restaurant recruits her. Lol. 💜 💰  -Brittany

We went a second time, we found hair on his food... call the manager, and he said it's not hair, it's a thread from the rice bag which was a lie. After we were escorted to a table, we waited 20 minutes. There was 2 waiters, none of them acknowledge us. It seemed like they were not even happy at all. We were tired of waiting. We just got up and left the restaurant. The vibe there is different. I feel like something is off. Somebody need to investigate this place. By the way, do not order sushi to go, they will give you a pre made meal stored from the fridge. (Like store bought sushi) The skin they use to make the sushi is chewy. I don't  usually do reviews but this has been on my mind since last time I went there (3 weeks ago).By the way, the food there has great taste. Just watch out for hair and how they treat you. Won't be going back there for sure. We used to spend $60-80 each visit.
